you have any papers that relate to your career,

09:10.532 --> 09:26.969
particularly as a student and or as an employee, 
and if you have any letters that you wrote home from

09:10.532 --> 09:26.969
overseas, if you would let them. Well, does 
anybody in the family have any? I doubt it. See, my

09:31.001 --> 09:32.403
family's all passed away. Because I thought if 
there was any V-mail or anything like that. I don't

09:37.150 --> 09:43.060
imagine so, because my family's all been doing 
some law, and their kids have everything. But if

09:43.080 --> 09:53.396
you do, because, you see, if we can gather all of 
those materials up, the more we can learn about

09:43.080 --> 09:53.396
this school, the better we can make it go in the 
future. The only thing that I've got... And I will

09:55.043 --> 09:57.386
go through my follow-up. I don't know, but I just 
went through the letters. I got the letters. Every

10:00.090 --> 10:04.456
year, the letter that I got September 1st 
announced what my salary was going to be. I got that

10:04.476 --> 10:06.819
all the way through my career. I'll have to look, 
but I might have some stuff there. Okay, then the

10:10.865 --> 10:11.906
last thing. In your heart now, as you look back, 
what parts of Texas A&M are dearest to you? Well,

10:20.237 --> 10:20.798
the university. No, but what parts of the 
university? I consider the university a part of

10:23.360 --> 10:26.343
Texas A&M. But if I were to come to you and ask... Oh, 
I think engineering. The engineering? Any

10:30.868 --> 10:32.429
particular part of engineering? Well, no, I think 
the... I can't say about the last 10 years. This is

10:38.415 --> 10:41.939
based on the last 10 years. The engineering school 
at Texas A&M University throughout the state of

10:43.240 --> 10:51.088
Texas, and I've traveled it all my life, both in 
industrial economics and in the Texas A&M. They

10:51.946 --> 10:55.231
were known as problem solvers. And people looked 
upon P&M's engineering thing as a place you'd come

10:55.251 --> 11:02.862
forward to get a problem answered, not to get some 
damn theory. And I was always extremely proud. And

11:06.708 --> 11:13.038
I was always proud of the fact that they were all 
very professional with it. I mean, they looked the

11:13.058 --> 11:14.099
part. And I was always proud to say that I was from 
the engineering company. Always. None of them

11:20.589 --> 11:21.210
knew me. But I always felt that they had to be 
respected and stayed down. Of course,

11:26.184 --> 11:33.153
agriculture has a strong, or did at that time have a 
very strong, and you can see why. Because you've

11:33.393 --> 11:35.516
got to eat. And regardless of what you think about 
agriculture, still it was an important segment of

11:35.536 --> 11:40.062
their economy. But you've got to eat. You want an 
unhappy group of people, don't feed them. So

11:43.547 --> 11:48.674
whether you like them or don't like them, you've 
got to respect

11:43.547 --> 11:48.674
them. But I never...

